column2: Lots of rain - lake seems murky
Staff gauge installed 8/28 at depth of 1.20.
Highest level I've have ever seen for Pesabic Lake.
Lake is lowest he's ever seen
Clear- cool- and lake dropping slowly to lowest level in year.
Partly cloudy- calm- lake continues to drop- and it rained some during the morning.
Cloudy- no more bloom- water level about 1" below mark.
Algae blooms- lake is still going down in spite of recent rains.
Weeds better than previous years.- water so low gage is out of water
Clear- sunny- some areas that are usually weed covered are clear- weeds in spots- lake level too low to measure.
Lake is very clear due to lack of runoff
Ice on lake about 95% of surface- lake still going down.
Ice out 4/28- nicest day so far.
Lake up- clouded with run-off from rains.
Recent rain has raised level somewhat- still low
Lake level so low that can't get close to gauge- reading taken from distance.
Lake dropping fast- a little above last year- weeds.
Last report- took boat out due to low water.
Clear- calm- lots of floating weeds
About 6" rain recently- lots of floating weeds make visibility difficult
Sunny- clear- grass clippings in lake- can't find source
Sunny- warm- still weeds + grass clippings- fishing good
Clear- sunny- calm- algae starting to bloom
Clear- little wind- weeds along shore turning brown
Ice out: 4/7- level highest in 6 years.
Water clear- few weeds- little swimming.
Weeds are dying- not much swimming
Clear- sunshine- slight breeze- much clearer lake than before.
Air temp is 63 degrees- sunny and light breeze.
Winds are southwest and it is 83 degrees.
Ice off April 5th- 1998- weather 86 degrees F- partly cloudy- and west/southwest wind.
Mid 80s- west winds- and 10-20 mph wind.
Temperature is 76 degrees and southwest wind.
The temperature is 82 degrees F- water surface temperature is 73.4 degrees and bottom temperature is 72.5 degrees.
The temperature is 78 degrees.  Ice off on 4/16/2001.
Lots of weed growth to the surface
